oc:skill_python_scala_translation_python_scala_idioms a oc:DeclarativeSkill,
        oc:Skill ;
    dcterms:identifier "python-scala-idioms" ;
    skos:broader "Translation guide" ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom ".agents/skills/skillsbench/python-scala-translation/python-scala-idioms" ;
    oc:contentHash "7a81f13422fe4612220fe17870aa76ae803acd15c08236c5ca6664dd7adb123d" ;
    oc:differentia "that teaches idiomatic Scala patterns when translating from Python, emphasizing immutability, expression-based style, sealed hierarchies, and Scala conventions" ;
    oc:extends oc:skill_ontoskills_python_scala_syntax_mapping ;
    oc:handlesFailure oc:InvalidInput ;
    oc:hasArgumentHint "Python code or pattern to translate idiomatically to Scala" ;
    oc:hasCategory "development" ;
    oc:hasDescription "Guide for writing idiomatic Scala when translating from Python. Use when the goal is not just syntactic translation but producing clean, idiomatic Scala code. Covers immutability, expression-based style, sealed hierarchies, and common Scala conventions." ;
    oc:hasName "python-scala-idioms" ;
    oc:hasSection [ a oc:Section ;
            oc:hasSubsection [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:Table ;
                            oc:blockType "table" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:rowCount 13 ;
                            oc:tableCaption "## Cheat Sheet: Common Transformations" ;
                            oc:tableMarkdown """| Python Pattern | Idiomatic Scala |
|---------------|-----------------|
| `if x is None` | `x.isEmpty` or pattern match |
| `if x is not None` | `x.isDefined` or `x.nonEmpty` |
| `x if x else default` | `x.getOrElse(default)` |
| `[x for x in xs if p(x)]` | `xs.filter(p)` |
| `[f(x) for x in xs]` | `xs.map(f)` |
| `any(p(x) for x in xs)` | `xs.exists(p)` |
| `all(p(x) for x in xs)` | `xs.forall(p)` |
| `next(x for x in xs if p(x), None)` | `xs.find(p)` |
| `dict(zip(keys, values))` | `keys.zip(values).toMap` |
| `isinstance(x, Type)` | `x.isInstanceOf[Type]` or pattern match |
| `try: ... except: ...` | `Try { ... }` or pattern match |
| Mutable accumulator loop | `foldLeft` / `foldRight` |
| `for i, x in enumerate(xs)` | `xs.zipWithIndex` |
""" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 12 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Cheat Sheet: Common Transformations" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// DON'T: Use null
val name: String = null  // Bad!

// DO: Use Option
val name: Option[String] = None

// DON'T: Use Any or type casts
val data: Any = getData()
val name = data.asInstanceOf[String]

// DO: Use proper types and pattern matching
sealed trait Data
case class UserData(name: String) extends Data
val data: Data = getData()
data match {
  case UserData(name) => // use name
}

// DON'T: Nested if-else chains
if (x == 1) ... else if (x == 2) ... else if (x == 3) ...

// DO: Pattern matching
x match {
  case 1 => ...
  case 2 => ...
  case 3 => ...
}

// DON'T: var with mutation
var total = 0
for (x <- items) total += x

// DO: fold
val total = items.sum
// or
val total = items.foldLeft(0)(_ + _)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 302-339" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 13 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Anti-Patterns to Avoid" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - separate side effects
val items = (0 until 10).map(_ * 2).toList
items.foreach(x => println(s"Value: $x"))

// Or use tap for debugging
val items = (0 until 10)
  .map(_ * 2)
  .tapEach(x => println(s"Value: $x"))
  .toList
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 156-166" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
items = []
for x in range(10):
    items.append(x * 2)
    print(f"Added {x * 2}")
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 148-154" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 7 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Avoid Side Effects in Expressions" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - immutable approach
case class Counter(count: Int = 0) {
  def increment: Counter = copy(count = count + 1)
}

// Usage
val c1 = Counter()
val c2 = c1.increment  // Counter(1)
val c3 = c2.increment  // Counter(2)
// c1 is still Counter(0)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 31-42" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python - mutable by default
class Counter:
    def __init__(self):
        self.count = 0

    def increment(self):
        self.count += 1
        return self.count
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 20-29" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 2 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Immutability First" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
result = []
for item in items:
    if item.active:
        result.append(item.value * 2)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 131-137" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - use collection methods
val result = items
  .filter(_.active)
  .map(_.value * 2)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 139-144" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 6 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Prefer Methods on Collections" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - named parameters work the same
def createUser(
  name: String,
  email: String,
  admin: Boolean = false,
  active: Boolean = true
): User = ???

val user = createUser("Alice", "alice@example.com", admin = true)

// Case class with defaults is often better
case class User(
  name: String,
  email: String,
  admin: Boolean = false,
  active: Boolean = true
)

val user = User("Alice", "alice@example.com", admin = true)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 178-198" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
def create_user(name, email, admin=False, active=True):
    pass

user = create_user("Alice", "alice@example.com", admin=True)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 170-176" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 8 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Use Named Parameters for Clarity" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - expression-based
def getStatus(code: Int): String = code match {
  case 200 => "OK"
  case 404 => "Not Found"
  case _ => "Unknown"
}

// No intermediate variable, match is an expression
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 58-67" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python - statement-based
def get_status(code):
    if code == 200:
        status = "OK"
    elif code == 404:
        status = "Not Found"
    else:
        status = "Unknown"
    return status
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 46-56" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 3 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Expression-Based Style" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - consider returning useful information
def saveUser(user: User): Either[Error, UserId] = {
  db.save(user) match {
    case Right(id) => Right(id)
    case Left(err) => Left(err)
  }
}

// Or at minimum, use Try
def saveUser(user: User): Try[Unit] = Try {
  db.save(user)
}
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 240-253" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python - None return is common
def save_user(user):
    db.save(user)
    # implicit None return
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 233-238" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 10 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Avoid Returning Unit" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
def find_user(id):
    user = db.get(id)
    if user is None:
        return None
    profile = user.get("profile")
    if profile is None:
        return None
    return profile.get("email")
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 102-112" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - Option chaining
def findUser(id: Int): Option[String] = for {
  user <- db.get(id)
  profile <- user.profile
  email <- profile.email
} yield email

// Or with flatMap
def findUser(id: Int): Option[String] =
  db.get(id)
    .flatMap(_.profile)
    .flatMap(_.email)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 114-127" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 5 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Replace Null Checks with Option" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python - loose typing
def process_payment(method: str, amount: float):
    if method == "credit":
        # process credit
        pass
    elif method == "debit":
        # process debit
        pass
    elif method == "crypto":
        # process crypto
        pass
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 71-83" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - sealed trait for exhaustive matching
sealed trait PaymentMethod
case class CreditCard(number: String, expiry: String) extends PaymentMethod
case class DebitCard(number: String) extends PaymentMethod
case class Crypto(walletAddress: String) extends PaymentMethod

def processPayment(method: PaymentMethod, amount: Double): Unit = method match {
  case CreditCard(num, exp) => // process credit
  case DebitCard(num) => // process debit
  case Crypto(addr) => // process crypto
}
// Compiler warns if you miss a case!
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 85-98" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 4 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Sealed Hierarchies for Domain Modeling" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
class Parser:
    def __init__(self, config):
        self.config = config

    @classmethod
    def default(cls):
        return cls(Config())
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 257-266" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala - companion object with apply
class Parser(config: Config)

object Parser {
  def apply(config: Config): Parser = new Parser(config)
  def apply(): Parser = new Parser(Config())
}

// Usage
val parser = Parser()  // Calls apply()
val parser = Parser(customConfig)
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 268-280" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 11 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Use Apply for Factory Methods" ],
                [ a oc:Section ;
                    oc:hasContent [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """# Python
MAX_RETRY_COUNT = 3
def calculate_total_price(items):
    pass

class ShoppingCart:
    def __init__(self):
        self._items = []
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "python" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 2 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 210-219" ],
                        [ a oc:Table ;
                            oc:blockType "table" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 1 ;
                            oc:rowCount 5 ;
                            oc:tableCaption "## Scala Naming Conventions" ;
                            oc:tableMarkdown """| Python | Scala |
|--------|-------|
| `snake_case` (variables, functions) | `camelCase` |
| `SCREAMING_SNAKE` (constants) | `CamelCase` or `PascalCase` |
| `PascalCase` (classes) | `PascalCase` |
| `_private` | `private` keyword |
| `__very_private` | `private[this]` |
""" ],
                        [ a oc:CodeExample ;
                            oc:blockType "code_block" ;
                            oc:codeContent """// Scala
val MaxRetryCount = 3  // or final val MAX_RETRY_COUNT
def calculateTotalPrice(items: List[Item]): Double = ???

class ShoppingCart {
  private var items: List[Item] = Nil
}
""" ;
                            oc:codeLanguage "scala" ;
                            oc:contentOrder 3 ;
                            oc:sourceLocation "lines 221-229" ] ;
                    oc:sectionLevel 2 ;
                    oc:sectionOrder 9 ;
                    oc:sectionTitle "Scala Naming Conventions" ],
